eers-education-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyoung%20people%20pursing%20trades%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20construction%20companies%20have%20tried%20to%20draw%20more%20people%20to%20the%20field%20with%20proactive%20recruiting%20efforts%20and%20higher%20wages%20%E2%80%94%20including%20trying%20to%20attract%20workers%20from%20out%20of%20state.%20Montana%20has%20already%20lured%20a%20high%20number%20transplants%20in%20part%20due%20to%20a%20relatively%20lower%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20especially%20when%20compared%20to%20a%20state%20like%20California%2C%20where%20many%20have%20moved%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIan%20Baylon%2C%20a%20tradesman%20from%20California%2C%20told%20BI%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20when%20he%20visited%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmontana-transplant-priced-out-of-california-housing-yellowstone-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMontana%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022%20and%20was%20considering%20moving%20there%2C%20he%20decided%20on%20a%20whim%20to%20see%20if%20anyone%20was%20hiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20reached%20out%20to%20a%20company%20about%20an%20opening%2C%20they%20quickly%20invited%20him%20in%20for%20an%20interview.%20A%20week%20later%20when%20he%20was%20back%20home%2C%20they%20offered%20him%20the%20job%20%E2%80%94%20matching%20his%20Bay%20Area%20salary%2C%20plus%20moving%20costs%20and%20other%20perks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Montana%2C%20wage%20growth%20in%20construction%20grew%20annually%20by%20an%20average%20of%200.6%25%20from%202020%20to%202023%2C%20according%20to%20the%20state%20government%20report%2C%20with%20an%20average%20salary%20of%20%2467%2C386.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20some%20say%20the%20growth%20in%20wages%20has%20not%20been%20enough%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20rising%20costs%20of%20living%20in%20the%20state.%20An%20analysis%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconstructioncoverage.com%2Fresearch%2Fwhere-construction-workers-would-have-to-work-longest-to-afford-home%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EConstruction%20Coverage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20industry%20site%20that%20reviews%20construction%20software%20and%20other%20services%2C%20found%20the%20average%20construction%20worker%20in%20Montana%20would%20need%20to%20work%2068%20hours%20a%20week%20to%20afford%20a%20median-priced%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225120%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20men%20standing%20next%20to%20earthmover%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675cf38552dd0818d1a741bb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223413%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EConstruction%20employment%20in%20Montana%20is%20growing%20faster%20than%20other%20states%20but%20contractors%20still%20can't%20fill%20all%20their%20open%20roles.%3Cp%3ENoah%20Clayton%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22481dfba4-bfce-48bf-aec4-261ff816bcfd%5C%22%3EApprenticeship%20programs%20allow%20young%20workers%20to%20'earn%20and%20learn'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20of%20the%20largest%20contractors%20in%20Montana%20told%20BI%20that%20folks%20interested%20in%20getting%20into%20construction%20do%20not%20need%20any%20experience%20in%20the%20industry%20to%20get%20hired%20%E2%80%94%20they%20can%20learn%20on%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20of%20both%20companies%2C%20Dick%20Anderson%20and%20Sletten%20Construction%2C%20said%20they%20also%20have%20dedicated%20apprenticeship%20programs%20that%20are%20a%20draw%20for%20new%20workers%20to%20the%20field%2C%20especially%20young%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERyan%2C%20of%20Dick%20Anderson%2C%20said%20he%20was%20hired%20by%20the%20company%20in%202021%20to%20develop%20an%20education%20program%20that%20would%20help%20attract%20and%20retain%20employees.%20The%20four-year%20apprenticeship%20program%20allows%20employees%20to%20work%20and%20earn%20while%20also%20enrolling%20in%20classes%20at%20a%20college%20they%20partner%20with.%20Students%20who%20complete%20the%20program%20can%20come%20out%20of%20it%20with%20an%20associates%20degree%2C%20real%20work%20experience%2C%20and%20actual%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20jobs%20in%20construction%20do%20not%20require%20an%20associates%20degree%2C%20Ryan%20said%20they%20can%20help%20with%20career%20advancement%20and%20promotions%2C%20as%20well%20as%20satisfy%20a%20desire%20to%20pursue%20some%20level%20of%20college.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20are%20talking%20to%20young%20people%20and%20mom%20and%20dad%20are%20saying%2C%20'You're%20not%20going%20to%20work.%20You%20need%20to%20go%20to%20college%2C'%20we%20can%20at%20least%20say%2C%20'Well%2C%20what%20if%20they're%20doing%20both%20at%20the%20same%20time%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichelle%20Cohens%2C%20who%20works%20in%20human%20resource%20management%20at%20Sletten%2C%20said%20the%20company%20also%20has%20a%20four-year%20apprenticeship%20program%20that%20allows%20employees%20to%20%26quot%3Bearn%20and%20learn.%26quot%3B%20Employees%20in%20the%20program%20also%20take%20a%20week%20several%20times%20a%20year%20to%20do%20trainings%20with%20the%20union%2C%20and%20then%20come%20back%20and%20hop%20right%20back%20into%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20companies%20said%20they've%20developed%20relationships%20with%20high%20schools%20and%20high%20school%20educators%20to%20help%20reach%20young%20people%2C%20who%20they%20said%20seem%20increasingly%20open%20to%20forgoing%20college%20and%20considering%20trades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20several%20years%20of%20trying%20to%20get%20in%20front%20of%20students%2C%20Cohens%20said%20the%20efforts%20do%20seem%20to%20be%20paying%20off%2C%20with%20more%20reaching%20out%20about%20jobs.%20She%20said%20young%20people%20are%20drawn%20in%20by%20the%20chance%20to%20work%20with%20their%20hands%20rather%20than%20sit%20at%20a%20computer%20all%20day%2C%20and%20the%20chance%20to%20avoid%20taking%20on%20student%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20highlight%20how%20good%20paying%20jobs%20they%20are%2C%20how%20you%20can%20get%20into%20the%20trades%20right%20out%20of%20high%20school%20or%20without%20any%20true%20knowledge%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20paying%20us%20to%20learn%2C%20we're%20paying%20you%20to%20learn.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Smith%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Montana%20Contractors'%20Association%2C%20said%20companies%20are%20also%20evolving%20their%20culture%20to%20meet%20Gen%20Z%20workers%20where%20they're%20at.%20Young%20people%20today%2C%20he%20said%2C%20don't%20necessarily%20want%20to%20work%2055%20hour%20weeks%20in%20the%20summer.%20They%20want%20breaks.%20They%20want%20to%20take%20time%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20five%20or%20ten%20years%20contractors%20have%20realized%20%26quot%3Byou%20can't%20just%20throw%20a%20job%20out%20there%20and%20say%2C%20'Hey%2C%20we%20pay%20big%20wages%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20to%20have%20other%20things%2C%20and%20the%20construction%20world%20has%20to%20think%20differently%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20news%20tip%20or%20a%20story%20to%20share%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Akvlamis%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ekvlamis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmontana-contractors-construction-labor-shortage-attract-get-z-trades-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734185521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675cdc85cf8d1359a2e015b5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmontana-contractors-construction-labor-shortage-attract-get-z-trades-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Montana%20contractors%20are%20trying%20to%20encourage%20more%20Gen%20Zers%20to%20go%20into%20trades%20to%20address%20t