D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fdelectable_reveries%2Fp%2FCUm20jMI-Y6%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVernika%20Awal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20(R)%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fdelhifoodtwins%2Fp%2FCrP5ocdPipd%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDelhi%20Food%20Twins%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20on%20one%20visit%20to%20Mandi%20House%20that%20food%20consultant%20Taiyaba%20Ali%20stumbled%20upon%20a%20humble%20%3Cem%3Echai%20%3C%2Fem%3Estall%20right%20outside%20the%20Shri%20Ram%20Centre%20for%20Performing%20Arts.%20Here%2C%20she%20discovered%20the%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CI%20found%20the%20place%20one%20winter%20evening%20while%20walking%20around%20Mandi%20House%20with%20my%20partner.%20It%20almost%20became%20a%20%3Cem%3Echai%20%3C%2Fem%3Esamosa%20date.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E2.%20Dadu%20Cutlet%20Shop%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLove%20at%20first%20bite%E2%80%9D%20is%20how%20food%20writer%20Parul%20Pratap%20describes%20the%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%20%3C%2Fem%3Eshe%20sampled%20from%20the%20eatery%20in%20Chittaranjan%20Park%20in%20Delhi.%20%E2%80%9CI%20grew%20up%20eating%20Punjabi%20%3Cem%3Esamosas%20%3C%2Fem%3Esince%20I%20was%20born%20and%20brought%20up%20in%20Delhi.%20But%20in%20the%20early%2090%E2%80%99s%2C%20my%20dad%E2%80%99s%20elder%20brother%20built%20his%20home%20in%20C%20R%20Park%20and%20I%20tried%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F80824%2Fsamosa-history-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBengali%20samosa%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Efor%20the%20first%20time.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fplugins%2Fvideo.php%3Fheight%3D314%26href%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.facebook.com%252FDelhiFoodWalks%252